How div is Used to Build a Webpage Layout
Developers divide a webpage into sections using div.

Example structure:
Header
Navigation
Main Content
Sidebar
Footer

Example HTML:
                    <div class="header">Header</div>
                    
                    <div class="nav">Navigation</div>
                    
                    <div class="main">
                        <div class="content">Main Content</div>
                        <div class="sidebar">Sidebar</div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="footer">Footer</div>

Each <div> represents a section of the page.
CSS can then control the position, size, colors, etc.

